data.title: great guatelaman foood
data.text: my favorite is carne adoba, it comes with rice, beans, salad and tortillas.. it has great flavor and they serve a large potion.

data.title: Not bad., but not great.
data.text: We have been here a few times. The food is usually good and portion sizes are decent for the price. The last time we went however, the waitress was incredibly rude. She got our order totally wrong. We waited a very long time for our food and when it came out, it was cold. The waitress never came to check and see if we needed anything else. And there was no manager available to speak to about our issues with the service. Needless to say, we have not been back since then.

data.title: Awesome food at great prices.
data.text: One of the best meals we had in a long time. Unique, authentic and delicious! Family Restaurant...if you are in the area you can go wrong. We are looking forward to coming  back.
